---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Maintain Long-Term Governance, Not One-Time Trust"
  description="Treat trust as something sustained through ongoing oversight, updates, and responsiveness—not a one-time promise. Design for continuous monitoring, improvement, and communication about how the system is governed."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Long-term governance" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Ongoing Transparency</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >How we govern this AI: We review feedback weekly, publish incident summaries quarterly,
            and update our model and policies when we find issues. [Governance overview] [Latest
            report]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Users see that the system is actively monitored and updated; governance is visible, not
            static.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Updates and Change Communication</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >We've updated our recommendation logic (March 2024) based on user feedback and new
            policy. [What changed] [Contact us with questions]</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >When behavior or policy changes, users are informed and can understand the impact.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Set-and-Forget (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >"We're committed to responsible AI" on launch, but no public updates on incidents,
            model changes, or policy. No way to see if feedback led to improvements. Trust is
            assumed, not maintained.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Trust degrades when users see no evidence of ongoing oversight or improvement after the
            first promise.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Governance in Practice</b></mds-text>
          <div class="grid gap-300">
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Publish or link to governance practices, incident summaries, and how feedback
                is used</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Communicate when models or policies change in ways that affect user-facing
                behavior</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Don't:</b> Rely on a one-time "Responsible AI" statement with no follow-through or
                visibility</mds-text
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Provide ongoing visibility into how the AI is monitored, updated, and governed—e.g. reports,
      change logs, or governance pages.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Treat trust as established once at launch with no further communication about oversight or
      improvement.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      When models or policies change in ways that affect users, communicate what changed and where
      to learn more.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Deploy updates or policy changes silently when they can affect user expectations or outcomes.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
